3.02 Termination of Membership  
A Membership in the Society is terminated when:  
a.	the Member dies, or, in the case of a Member that is a corporation, the corporation is 
dissolved;  
b.	a Member fails to maintain any qualifications for Membership described in Section 2.01 
of these By-Laws;  
c.	the Member resigns by delivering a written resignation to the Vice President of Finance 
and Administration of the Society in which case such resignation shall be effective on the 
date received;  
d.

Unless so removed, an Executive shall hold 
office until the earlier of:  
a.	April 30; 
b.	the Executive's resignation;  
c.	such Executive ceasing to be a Director (if a necessary qualification of appointment);  d. 
such Executive's death.
